# Internationalization (i18n) Patterns

## I18n Architecture Overview

This project uses a **cookie-based locale management system** without URL-based routing, as specified in user preferences. The implementation uses next-intl with custom locale utilities.

### Supported Locales

Configured in [src/constants/locale.ts](mdc:src/constants/locale.ts):

```typescript
export const LOCALE_CONFIG = {
  en: { label: "English", flag: "🇺🇸", dir: "ltr" },
  vi: { label: "Tiếng Việt", flag: "🇻🇳", dir: "ltr" },
} as const;

export const DEFAULT_LOCALE = "en";
export const LOCALE_COOKIE_NAME = "NEXT_LOCALE";
```

## Translation Structure

### Translation Files Organization

```
src/locales/
├── en/                    # English translations
│   ├── auth.json         # Authentication-related text
│   ├── form.json         # Form labels and validation
│   └── metadata.json     # Page titles and descriptions
├── vi/                    # Vietnamese translations
│   ├── auth.json         # Same structure as English
│   ├── form.json
│   └── metadata.json
├── utils/                 # Locale utilities
│   ├── client.ts         # Client-side locale functions
│   └── server.ts         # Server-side locale functions
└── request.ts            # Next-intl configuration
```

### Translation File Structure

Each translation file follows a nested structure:

```json
// form.json example
{
  "login": {
    "title": "Sign In",
    "description": "Enter your credentials to access your account",
    "email": "Email or Username",
    "password": "Password",
    "forgotPassword": "Forgot your password?"
  },
  "common": {
    "form": {
      "required": "{field} is required",
      "min": "Must be at least {length} characters",
      "max": "Must be no more than {length} characters"
    }
  }
}
```

## Next-intl Configuration

### Request Configuration

[src/locales/request.ts](mdc:src/locales/request.ts) handles:

- **Dynamic locale detection** from cookies
- **Message loading** for current locale
- **Namespace organization** (form, metadata, auth)

```typescript
export default getRequestConfig(async () => {
  const locale = await getServerLocale();
  return {
    locale,
    messages: {
      form: (await import(`../locales/${locale}/form.json`)).default,
      metadata: (await import(`../locales/${locale}/metadata.json`)).default,
      auth: (await import(`../locales/${locale}/auth.json`)).default,
    },
  };
});
```

### Next.js Integration

[next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) includes next-intl plugin:

```typescript
const withNextIntl = createNextIntlPlugin("./src/locales/request.ts");
export default withNextIntl(nextConfig);
```

## Locale Management System

### Server-Side Locale Utilities

[src/locales/utils/server.ts](mdc:src/locales/utils/server.ts):

```typescript
// Get current locale from cookies
export async function getServerLocale(): Promise<SupportedLocale> {
  const cookieStore = await cookies();
  const locale = cookieStore.get(LOCALE_COOKIE_NAME)?.value;
  return SUPPORTED_LOCALES.includes(locale) ? locale : DEFAULT_LOCALE;
}

// Set locale cookie server-side
export async function setServerLocale(locale: SupportedLocale): Promise<void> {
  const cookieStore = await cookies();
  cookieStore.set(LOCALE_COOKIE_NAME, locale, {
    expires: LOCALE_COOKIE_EXPIRES,
    path: "/",
    sameSite: "lax",
    secure: process.env.NODE_ENV === "production",
  });
}
```

### Client-Side Locale Utilities

[src/locales/utils/client.ts](mdc:src/locales/utils/client.ts):

```typescript
// Get current locale from cookies
export function getClientLocale(): SupportedLocale {
  const locale = Cookies.get(LOCALE_COOKIE_NAME);
  return SUPPORTED_LOCALES.includes(locale) ? locale : DEFAULT_LOCALE;
}

// Set locale and reload page
export function setClientLocale(locale: SupportedLocale): void {
  Cookies.set(LOCALE_COOKIE_NAME, locale, {
    expires: LOCALE_COOKIE_EXPIRES,
    path: "/",
    sameSite: "lax",
    secure: process.env.NODE_ENV === "production",
  });
  window.location.reload(); // Required for server-side locale change
}
```

## Locale Management Hook

### useLocaleManager Hook

[src/hooks/use-locale-manager.ts](mdc:src/hooks/use-locale-manager.ts):

```typescript
export function useLocaleManager() {
  const currentLocale = useLocale();
  const [isChanging, setIsChanging] = useState(false);

  const changeLocale = (newLocale: Locale) => {
    if (newLocale === currentLocale) return;
    setIsChanging(true);
    setClientLocale(newLocale); // Triggers page reload
  };

  return { locale: currentLocale, isChanging, changeLocale };
}
```

## Translation Usage Patterns

### In Components

```typescript
import { useTranslations } from "next-intl";

export function LoginForm() {
  const t = useTranslations("form"); // Namespace-specific translations

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{t("login.title")}</h1>
      <p>{t("login.description")}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### In Validation Schemas

```typescript
export const useLoginSchema = () => {
  const t = useTranslations();

  return z.object({
    email: z
      .string()
      .min(1, { error: t("form.common.form.required", { field: "Email" }) })
      .email({ error: t("form.common.form.invalidEmail") }),
  });
};
```

### With Interpolation

```typescript
// Translation with variables
t("form.common.form.min", { length: 6 });
// Result: "Must be at least 6 characters"

// Complex interpolation
t("form.validation.passwordMatch", {
  field1: t("form.common.name.password"),
  field2: t("form.common.name.confirmPassword"),
});
```

## Language Switcher Implementation

### Language Switcher Component

[src/components/common/language-switcher.tsx](mdc:src/components/common/language-switcher.tsx):

- **Dropdown selection** with flags and labels
- **Current locale highlighting**
- **Loading state** during locale change
- **Accessible** with proper ARIA labels

```typescript
export function LanguageSwitcher() {
  const { locale, isChanging, changeLocale } = useLocaleManager();

  return (
    <Select value={locale} onValueChange={changeLocale}>
      {SUPPORTED_LOCALES.map((loc) => (
        <SelectItem key={loc} value={loc}>
          {getLocaleFlag(loc)} {getLocaleLabel(loc)}
        </SelectItem>
      ))}
    </Select>
  );
}
```

## Provider Setup

### I18n Provider

[src/providers/i18n-provider.tsx](mdc:src/providers/i18n-provider.tsx):

```typescript
import { NextIntlClientProvider } from "next-intl";

export function I18nProvider({ children, messages, locale }) {
  return (
    <NextIntlClientProvider messages={messages} locale={locale}>
      {children}
    </NextIntlClientProvider>
  );
}
```

## Best Practices

### Translation Key Naming

- **Namespace structure**: `form.login.title`
- **Descriptive keys**: Avoid generic names like `text1`
- **Consistent nesting**: Group related translations
- **Action-based**: `button.save`, `error.validation`

### Message Organization

- **Feature-based**: Group by UI sections or features
- **Reusable common**: Extract common patterns
- **Validation messages**: Centralize form validation text
- **Error handling**: Consistent error message structure

### Performance Considerations

- **Namespace splitting**: Load only needed translations
- **Dynamic imports**: Lazy-load translation files
- **Cookie optimization**: Minimize cookie size
- **Cache headers**: Proper caching for translation files

### Accessibility

- **RTL support**: Ready for future right-to-left languages
- **Screen readers**: Proper ARIA labels for language switcher
- **Focus management**: Maintain focus after locale change
- **Language indication**: HTML lang attribute updates

## Common Patterns

### Form Error Messages

```typescript
// Standard validation with field name
t("form.common.form.required", { field: t("form.common.name.email") });

// Custom validation messages
t("form.register.validation.usernameOrEmailInvalid");

// Length constraints
t("form.common.form.min", { length: 3 });
t("form.common.form.max", { length: 20 });
```

### Success/Error Notifications

```typescript
// Success messages
toast.success(t("form.register.success"));

// Error messages with context
toast.error(ctx.error.message || t("form.common.error.generic"));
```

### Page Metadata

```typescript
// In page components
export async function generateMetadata() {
  const t = await getTranslations("metadata");
  return {
    title: t("login.title"),
    description: t("login.description"),
  };
}
```
